#
# Windows PowerShell script for AD DS Deployment
#

Import-Module ADDSDeployment
Install-ADDSForest `
-CreateDnsDelegation:$false `
-DatabasePath "C:\Windows\NTDS" `
-DomainMode "WinThreshold" `
-DomainName "ADDS.local" `
-DomainNetbiosName "ADDS" `
-ForestMode "WinThreshold" `
-InstallDns:$true `
-LogPath "C:\Windows\NTDS" `
-NoRebootOnCompletion:$false `
-SysvolPath "C:\Windows\SYSVOL" `
-Force:$true





✅ Step 1: Create a Virtual Machine in Azure
Go to Azure Portal
Click Virtual Machines → Create → Azure Virtual Machine
Fill details:
Resource Group → Create new (e.g., RG-ADDS)
VM Name → DC-VM
Region → Same as your resources
Image → Windows Server 2019/2022
Size → At least Standard B2s
Administrator Account:
Username: azureadmin
Password: Set strong password
Networking:
Create new Virtual Network
Example:
VNet: 10.0.0.0/16
Subnet: 10.0.0.0/24
Click Review + Create → Create
✅ Step 2: Set Static Private IP

After VM is created:

Go to VM → Networking
Click Network Interface
Go to IP Configuration
Change:
Private IP Assignment → Static
Save

👉 This is important because DC should not change IP.

✅ Step 3: Configure DNS to Point to Itself
Go to Virtual Network
Click DNS Servers
Select:
Custom
Add IP: (your DC private IP) (e.g., 10.0.0.4)
Save
✅ Step 4: Connect to VM (RDP)
Download RDP file
Login using admin credentials
✅ Step 5: Install AD DS Role

Inside VM:

Open Server Manager
Click:
Add Roles and Features
Select:
Role-based installation
Choose your VM
Select:
✅ Active Directory Domain Services
Click Next → Install
✅ Step 6: Promote VM to Domain Controller

After installation:

In Server Manager → Click:
⚠️ Promote this server to a domain controller
Choose:
✅ Add a new forest
Enter:
Root domain name: mydomain.local
Set:
DSRM password
Next → Install

👉 VM will restart automatically

✅ Step 7: Verify AD DS

After reboot:

Login as:

mydomain\azureadmin
Open:
Active Directory Users and Computers
Verify domain created successfully
✅ Step 8: Configure NSG (Important)

Allow required ports:

RDP → 3389
DNS → 53
LDAP → 389
Kerberos → 88
✅ Step 9: Join Other VM to Domain (Optional)
Create another VM
Set DNS → DC private IP
Go to:
System → Change settings → Domain

Enter:

mydomain.local
